16:00.000 --> 16:02.000
something that funders are really

16:02.000 --> 16:04.000
interested in, right? You're already building

16:04.000 --> 16:06.000
a world. So if you're

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
an event

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
person or a dancer,

16:10.000 --> 16:12.000
you probably are already

16:12.000 --> 16:14.000
bringing people together powerfully to like

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
connect to the community. And all

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
of that is like, you're already

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
creating a type of world.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
And I think the more you think of

16:22.000 --> 16:24.000
the work you're doing is something inherently

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
valuable. And

16:26.000 --> 16:28.000
the more it aligns with how you're already

16:28.000 --> 16:30.000
building a world,

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
it's also a really

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
great opportunity to show funders

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
that people are already doing things like

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
this. Because the thing is, like a lot

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
of funders and people without grants,

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
they sometimes are shy

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
about taking risks on untested

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
people or untested ideas.

16:46.000 --> 16:48.000
So the more you can say, the more you

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
do this, the more you're building this world,

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
the more successful you will be in

16:52.000 --> 16:54.000
finding funders who want to do

16:54.000 --> 16:56.000
the work that you are interested in

16:56.000 --> 16:58.000
doing. So now I'm going to

16:58.000 --> 17:00.000
connect it to Jeff to take us to our

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
next act, which is

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
a hero emerges.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.000
What does that mean, Jeff?

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
That's right. So, alright, so what do you understand

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
to your why, right? I think

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
the one thing I have made it into kind of is

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
your why lives in context

17:16.000 --> 17:18.000
not only the funders vision

17:18.000 --> 17:20.000
of the community that you create in, right?

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
And I think that's something important to

17:22.000 --> 17:24.000
help

17:24.000 --> 17:26.000
funders understand. I was writing a grant

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
for it, this was an arts grant, but someone was doing

17:28.000 --> 17:30.000
a statewide education program.

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
And the founder was in

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
Rhode Island, I think,

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
tiny state, right?

17:36.000 --> 17:38.000
Tiny, tiny state. And they

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
they

17:40.000 --> 17:42.000
this non-profit was like, I know

17:42.000 --> 17:44.000
we're a good fit. We've been in the community

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
for nine, five years in a row, but we're a good

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
fit. We want to bring you all in

17:48.000 --> 17:50.000
to help. How can we

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
get this? So I just called the founder and I was like, hey, what's up?

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
You have a friend of them, we think they're a good fit, too.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
Can you give us any feedback?

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
And they're like, well, we don't understand, like

17:58.000 --> 18:00.000
why do you need so much travel

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
and lodging and

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
food stipends, like

18:04.000 --> 18:06.000
why? And I was like, oh,

18:06.000 --> 18:08.000
you live in Rhode Island, so driving across

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
the state may just be you could

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
drive there and drive back in the same day.

18:12.000 --> 18:14.000
We're driving across the state of New Mexico

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
and that's at least a night, right?

18:16.000 --> 18:18.000
It's at least a day or if you're going from one corner

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
to the next, you're sending like multiple

18:20.000 --> 18:22.000
people, right? That's travel, that's

18:22.000 --> 18:24.000
hundreds of miles, that's lodging, that's right.

18:24.000 --> 18:26.000
So I don't think the funders

18:26.000 --> 18:28.000
understand the context in which you're creating

18:28.000 --> 18:30.000
and sometimes you're really powerful, especially

18:30.000 --> 18:32.000
if they're not from the state. So

18:32.000 --> 18:34.000
context, right? Why,

18:34.000 --> 18:36.000
where you're creating, the community you're creating within,

18:36.000 --> 18:38.000
and then the hero origins, right?

18:38.000 --> 18:40.000
Every story, like something,

18:40.000 --> 18:42.000
a hero, something happens to change the

18:42.000 --> 18:44.000
status quo, right?

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
Or address a problem that

18:46.000 --> 18:48.000
superhero music villain comes in

18:48.000 --> 18:50.000
and then the hero origins, right?

18:50.000 --> 18:52.000
That's you. That's your art.

18:52.000 --> 18:54.000
That's your community, depending

18:54.000 --> 18:56.000
on the thunder you're talking to.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.000
But mostly it's you, right?

18:58.000 --> 19:00.000
Your art, your

19:00.000 --> 19:02.000
creativity, you as an artist,

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
as the person who's going to change the conditions

19:04.000 --> 19:06.000
that the thunder is hoping

19:06.000 --> 19:08.000
changes in the world, right?

19:12.000 --> 19:14.000
And I think a lot of people misunderstand

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
funding as purely transactional,

19:16.000 --> 19:18.000
right? You kind of

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
feel like,

19:20.000 --> 19:22.000
please sir, can I have some more, right? Like

19:22.000 --> 19:24.000
money, please.

19:24.000 --> 19:26.000
But it's the opposite,

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
right? You're giving them an opportunity

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
to invest in

19:30.000 --> 19:32.000
the change, right?

19:32.000 --> 19:34.000
You're giving them an opportunity to invest in your art,

19:34.000 --> 19:36.000
which is cool, because you've already told them

19:36.000 --> 19:38.000
why it's cool, and

19:38.000 --> 19:40.000
you're giving them an opportunity. They will be selling

19:40.000 --> 19:42.000
that to fund you, right? That's a mindset shift

19:42.000 --> 19:44.000
that I think a lot of people can go into in funding.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.000
You're not going there begging for money.

19:46.000 --> 19:48.000
You're giving them an opportunity.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
And you're giving them an opportunity to partner with you,

19:50.000 --> 19:52.000
right? You're not going like,

19:52.000 --> 19:54.000
hey, give me money and then I'll go in

19:54.000 --> 19:56.000
and do my thing. Like, hey,

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
why don't we do this together?

19:58.000 --> 20:00.000
If you give them resources, and my talent,

20:00.000 --> 20:02.000
and my vision, we can change

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
the world. We can make the world a better

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
place, right? And that's what they want

20:06.000 --> 20:08.000
to hear. They don't want to just hear, like,

20:08.000 --> 20:10.000
I don't have any money,

20:10.000 --> 20:12.000
so I need some, please.

20:12.000 --> 20:14.000
They want to hear,

20:14.000 --> 20:16.000
I have a vision, and that visual

20:16.000 --> 20:18.000
aligns with your vision, and if you give me

20:18.000 --> 20:20.000
the resources to make this happen,

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
this is going to be amazing, and the world

20:22.000 --> 20:24.000
is going to be a better place for it, right?

20:24.000 --> 20:26.000
And there are also different ways

20:26.000 --> 20:28.000
to, like, some funders, it depends who they are,

20:28.000 --> 20:30.000
right? Some of them, like, on the website,

20:30.000 --> 20:32.000
they're like, please don't call us, please just

20:32.000 --> 20:34.000
submit the application, right? But sometimes you can

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
reach out to funders, especially if it's outside

20:36.000 --> 20:38.000
the funding cycle. That's a big tip.

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
If it's outside the funding cycle and they have contact

20:40.000 --> 20:42.000
information, call them, email

20:42.000 --> 20:44.000
them, right? Ask them, like,

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
this is my idea, this is my project,

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000
I think it's really cool, I think it's a fit, do you think it's

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
a fit? I don't know, sometimes I tell you,

20:50.000 --> 20:52.000
I'm like, eh, it's not really what we're looking for.

20:52.000 --> 20:54.000
We're like, I guess you should apply.

20:54.000 --> 20:56.000
Which isn't a guarantee, right? But you can follow

20:56.000 --> 20:58.000
those relationships.

21:00.000 --> 21:02.000
And there's a big difference. I've read so many grants

21:02.000 --> 21:04.000
that essentially are like, hey, give me a paintbrush

21:04.000 --> 21:06.000
so I can paint them.

21:06.000 --> 21:08.000
I want a paintbrush. And that makes

21:08.000 --> 21:10.000
sense, right? You're like, we need to talk

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
about what you're going to use their money for.

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
But you're not using their money for

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
a paintbrush, the paintbrush is a tool

21:16.000 --> 21:18.000
to

21:18.000 --> 21:20.000
paint a picture together.

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
You're asking them to paint a picture together.

21:22.000 --> 21:24.000
And of course, whatever your

21:24.000 --> 21:26.000
art form is.

21:26.000 --> 21:28.000
But if you're a visual artist, you're not asking

21:28.000 --> 21:30.000
for a paintbrush or a paint job canvas.

21:30.000 --> 21:32.000
You're asking them to paint a picture together.

21:32.000 --> 21:34.000
To partner with you.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
To get in on the ground floor.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.000
I was at a

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
workshop the other day and someone was like,

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
they

21:42.000 --> 21:44.000
went to a pitch competition that was

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
both, like, tech bros

21:46.000 --> 21:48.000
and artists.

21:48.000 --> 21:50.000
There was a huge difference. The tech bros would come out and be like,

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
you're so lucky and I'm here?

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
And you're so lucky you had the opportunity

21:54.000 --> 21:56.000
to invest in me.

21:56.000 --> 21:58.000
So they said that exactly.

21:58.000 --> 22:00.000
And I was like,

22:00.000 --> 22:02.000
hey,

22:02.000 --> 22:04.000
I'm so lucky to be here.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.000
And I really hope you like me.

22:06.000 --> 22:08.000
And that's the attitude

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
that a lot of people write funding proposals with.

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
I hope, please,

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
they save me money.

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
No, no, you're lucky

22:16.000 --> 22:18.000
you're in my application.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.000
The attitude, right?

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
I was like, I'm awesome.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
I'm super cool. This is amazing.

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
And all I need is your partnership

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
to make this thing amazing

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
and wouldn't it be cool if you had the opportunity

22:30.000 --> 22:32.000
to partner with me.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.000
By giving me the resources and unleashing my talent

22:34.000 --> 22:36.000
and my vision and creativity

22:36.000 --> 22:38.000
on the world.

22:38.000 --> 22:40.000
So some things to look at too, right?

22:40.000 --> 22:42.000
It's a relationship, right?

22:42.000 --> 22:44.000
Look at past funding.

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
Is your practice

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
and do you see yourself reflected

22:48.000 --> 22:50.000
in that funding industry?

22:50.000 --> 22:52.000
Particularly like the types of art

22:52.000 --> 22:54.000
or what the art is saying, right?

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
Do you see yourself reflected in some way?

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
Good indication that you might be a good applicant.

22:58.000 --> 23:00.000
If you don't, move on to the next one.

23:00.000 --> 23:02.000
Don't bang your head against the wall

23:02.000 --> 23:04.000
about finding opportunities that you already have

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
such a waste of time

23:06.000 --> 23:08.000
and don't do it right.

23:08.000 --> 23:10.000
Look at their funding history.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.000
Do their values

23:12.000 --> 23:14.000
match your values?

23:14.000 --> 23:16.000
Don't, also don't

23:16.000 --> 23:18.000
tie yourself in the knots

23:18.000 --> 23:20.000
going after something that doesn't match your values

23:20.000 --> 23:22.000
because then you're also going to be turning into a contract

23:22.000 --> 23:24.000
where you have to do the work that you said you were going to do

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
and you're going to be doing work that conflicts with your values

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
and I agree with that as well.

23:28.000 --> 23:30.000
That's great.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.000
But that's going to really tighten the knots.

23:32.000 --> 23:34.000
So do their values, can you genuinely

23:34.000 --> 23:36.000
connect with their values?

23:36.000 --> 23:38.000
That means they can probably genuinely connect with their values.

23:38.000 --> 23:40.000
And then is there a line in the overlap

23:40.000 --> 23:42.000
between the vision that they want to see?

23:42.000 --> 23:44.000
They'll tell you straight up

23:44.000 --> 23:46.000
this funding is to do this.

23:46.000 --> 23:48.000
Can you do that with your heart?

23:48.000 --> 23:50.000
And how can you tell them that you can do that

23:50.000 --> 23:52.000
with your heart?

23:52.000 --> 23:54.000
Maybe one thing I can also add

23:54.000 --> 23:56.000
to that, Jeff, is

23:56.000 --> 23:58.000
why don't you start thinking

23:58.000 --> 24:00.000
relationally or

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
rather than transactionally

24:02.000 --> 24:04.000
then the funding

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
opportunities and the work and the impact

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
usually goes beyond funding, right?

24:08.000 --> 24:10.000
So there have been many times

24:10.000 --> 24:12.000
where I haven't got the grant

24:12.000 --> 24:14.000
but it's turned to more work

24:14.000 --> 24:16.000
with that group because we were

24:16.000 --> 24:18.000
aligned and because it's clear

24:18.000 --> 24:20.000
that I was trying to build a world they were aligned with.

24:20.000 --> 24:22.000
And then the other side

24:22.000 --> 24:24.000
is like, I don't know

24:24.000 --> 24:26.000
if there's a couple of people from Santa Fe here

24:26.000 --> 24:28.000
but like they have this

24:28.000 --> 24:30.000
artist of solution grant

24:30.000 --> 24:32.000
and a lot of folks who get it

24:32.000 --> 24:34.000
usually get more money.

24:34.000 --> 24:36.000
You know, it's not just a one time

24:36.000 --> 24:38.000
thing and

24:38.000 --> 24:40.000
you have the artist solution to dispose

24:40.000 --> 24:42.000
but often you can go out to the funder

24:42.000 --> 24:44.000
and you say, hey, here's the stuff you're doing together

24:44.000 --> 24:46.000
here's the world

24:46.000 --> 24:48.000
here's the world you're painting together

24:48.000 --> 24:50.000
so let's keep

24:50.000 --> 24:52.000
that alive.

24:52.000 --> 24:54.000
One more thing to add

24:54.000 --> 24:56.000
that you made me think of.

24:56.000 --> 24:58.000
Let's keep the world alive.

24:58.000 --> 25:00.000
You get money sometimes

25:00.000 --> 25:02.000
you get some funding and another funder will

25:02.000 --> 25:04.000
be like, ooh that's very cool.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.000
So also have any awards, you can have

25:06.000 --> 25:08.000
any training you have, any other grants you've got

25:08.000 --> 25:10.000
any other residency fellowships

25:10.000 --> 25:12.000
like, you know, people are people, you're still

25:12.000 --> 25:14.000
around with people and you're like, oh someone else trusts them

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
and maybe they don't know who that fellowship came from

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
and someone else trusts them

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
